Yet , as the record showed , there were circumstances irrefragably indicating that some person had gained access to old Jaffrey Pyncheon's private apartments , at or near the moment of his death . 
Whencesoever originating , there now arose a theory that undertook so to account for these circumstances as to exclude the idea of Clifford's agency . 
According to this version of the story , Judge Pyncheon , exemplary as we have portrayed him in our narrative , was , in his youth , an apparently irreclaimable scapegrace . 
